speech.p:
asked the Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs (1)

what steps he has taken to call attention to the need for reforms in the United Nations, in particular by the creation by like-minded states, as suggested by the Prime Minister of Canada, of a small peace-keeping force on a permanent basis;

(2) what consultations have taken place with countries in Asia, Africa and Latin America regarding the possible use by them of a peace-keeping force on a permanent basis.
